    <p>Read against the field, the indicative band of $2,508&ndash;$2,617 psf for a <strong>brand-new, GFA-harmonised, MRT-doorstep, integrated-commercial</strong> launch looks competitive &mdash; well below the J&rsquo;den 2023 high, and roughly in line with Sora / Lakegarden Residences.</p>

    <h3>Two small trade-offs to model</h3>

    <ul>
      <li><strong>Standard 99-year leasehold.</strong> Like every GLS site, Lucerne Grand is a 99-year lease (from June 2025). The 98-year balance is healthy and there&rsquo;s zero immediate lease-decay drag, but buyers strictly hunting freehold legacy assets will rule this out on principle.</li>
      <li><strong>Living through the JLD build-out.</strong> The proximity to the Growth Hotspot is the point &mdash; but the flip side is real: residents will live near ongoing urban construction and infrastructure works over the next decade. For long-horizon holders that&rsquo;s the trade-off you&rsquo;re being paid for.</li>
    </ul>

