    <h2>Who is Lucerne Grand actually for?</h2>

    <p>With a 95% Investability Score, Lucerne Grand is one of the most well-rounded OCR launches we&rsquo;ve reviewed this cycle. The buyer profile is unusually broad &mdash; two distinct groups both have a strong fit:</p>

    <ul>
      <li><strong>Long-horizon capital-growth investors.</strong> The combination of a 3.69% projected gross yield, an exceptional 6,820-unit MOP upgrader pool for exit liquidity, the JLD growth-hotspot spillover, and the five-plot GLS pipeline rebenchmarking precinct pricing upward makes this an unusually defensive, high-growth OCR asset.</li>
      <li><strong>Family upgraders &amp; genuine homemakers.</strong> The 87-metre MRT walk, the 1-minute walk to Jurong Lake Gardens, the Lucerne Galleria commercial podium and the dual primary-school catchment (Rulang + Shuqun) together create one of the &ldquo;stickiest&rdquo; family addresses you can buy in the OCR.</li>
      <li><strong>Owner-occupiers who value walkability.</strong> The combination of doorstep MRT, doorstep retail and doorstep gardens is rare in any region &mdash; and is what produces resale liquidity through cycles.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>It&rsquo;s a weaker fit if your priority is a freehold legacy asset, or if you genuinely can&rsquo;t tolerate living near active construction zones for a multi-year stretch.</p>

    <p>As always, the responsible next step is to <em>see the data before you see the showflat</em>. Read the PrimeKey Report above, line it up against any other JLD or West-region shortlist you&rsquo;re considering, and decide on facts &mdash; not on the brochure&rsquo;s rendering quality.</p>

